nodes.text: The rock-vulture was a species of bird found on the planet Utapau in the Outer Rim Territories. In 19 BBY, the corpse of the Kaleesh cyborg Grievous—left lying on the landing platform where he was killed by Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi—was untouched by the local rock-vultures, who were apparently unable to stomach him.
Rock-vultures were first mentioned in Matthew Stover's 2005 novelization of the prequel trilogy film Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith.
